        <body>       

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>East Cliff Lodge&#44;<lb/>
                Ramsgate.<lb/></p>
            <p>13 July 1886&#44;<lb/>
                Dear and respected Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>I have just received your<lb/> esteemed Letter of the 29<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Ulto.<lb/> and find myself most<lb/> reluctantly obliged to say I am<lb/> unable to comply with the<lb/> request therein contained&#44;<lb/> I receive daily numerous<lb/> applications from at home<lb/> and abroad for pecuniary<lb/> assistance and from their<lb/> large number can attend to<lb/> only a portion of them.  I suppose<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>it is not generally &#91;&#63;&#93; in mind<lb/> that I succeeded to only one fourth<lb/> part of my late Uncle&#39;s Fortune<lb/> and which carried with it<lb/> pecuniary and other <del>duties</del><lb/> responsibilities which I readily<lb/> accepted and which I intend to<lb/> endeavour to carry out&#44;<lb/> A small or inconsiderable<lb/> subscription from me would<lb/> be inappropriate and of little<lb/> use.<lb/></p>
            <p>For the very object you have<lb/> in view for the United States<lb/> Sir Moses has devoted for this<lb/> country&#44; jointly with a<lb/> Synagogue&#45;&#45;a sum of &#163;1000000<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>I am glad to know that<lb/> you have in your country<lb/> a large number of well<lb/> disposed and wealthy Jews&#44;<lb/> hence there should be no<lb/> difficulty in raising Funds<lb/> for such an excellent<lb/> Institution as you desire<lb/> to establish&#44; and you will<lb/> perhaps allow me to say<lb/> that we do not receive or<lb/> expect American support for<lb/> our English Institutions&#45;&#45;<lb/> I hold you personally in<lb/> so much esteem I am<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>really very sorry not to<lb/> comply with your request<lb/> but I have found it due<lb/> to you to trouble you<lb/> with the foregoing explanation.<lb/></p>
            <p>I remain&#44;<lb/>
                Yours faithfully<lb/>
                Joseph Sebag Montefiore<lb/></p>
                
            <p>To<lb/>
                The Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. S. Morais<lb/> &#38;c &#38;c<lb/></p>
            </body>
